results.name: Trajectory of 48 under prime factor concatenation procedure.
link: Sean A. Irvine, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..54
example: 48 = 2*2*2*2*3, so the next terms are 2,2,2,2,3; 22223 = 71*313, so the next terms are 71, 313; 71313 = 3*11*2161, so then we get 3, 11, 2161; etc.
